Step 1 – Create Project Folder
Create a new folder:
my-module
Open terminal inside it.

Step 2 – Initialize Node Project
Run:
•	npm init
It will ask questions:
Example answers:
package name: my-module
version: 1.0.0
description: simple math module
entry point: index.js
author: Your Name
This creates:
package.json

 Step 3 – Create Module File
Create file:
index.js
Example module code:
function add(a,b){
    return a+b
}

function multiply(a,b){
    return a*b
}

module.exports = {
    add,
    multiply
}
Explanation
This module exports two functions:
Function	Purpose
add()	adds numbers
multiply()	multiplies numbers


 Step 4 – Test the Module
Create another file:
test.js
Write:
const math = require('./index')

console.log(math.add(5,3))
console.log(math.multiply(4,2))
Run:
node test.js
Output:
8
8


Step 5 – Create npm Account
Go to:
https://www.npmjs.com
Create an account.

 Step 6 – Login to npm
In terminal run:
npm login
Enter:
username
password
email

Step 7 – Publish Module
Run:
npm publish
If successful you will see:
+ my-module@1.0.0
Now your module is available on npm registry.

Step 8 – Use Your Module in Another Project
Create new project and install:
npm install my-module
Use it:
const math = require('my-module')

console.log(math.add(10,5))
